                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2579: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-22T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Stevens:</p>
                <p>Your June 18, 11 a.m. In my June 15, 4 p.m., I had in mind primarily suggestions
                    on your part as to measures for protecting the financial advances made by this
                    Government in connection with your work and also any recommendations which you
                    might find it possible to make with respect to prevention of commercial
                    discrimination on the Chinese Eastern and in general the preservation of present
                    and future opportunities for American trade.</p>
                <p>Proposals to other governments may suggest complete termination of Allied
                    agreement or of Technical Board at least on its present basis and not merely
                    withdrawal of American representation.</p>
                <p>Definite course of action not yet determined beyond need for winding up
                    expenditures and I await your recommendations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
